# API Tests App — Core Rules

- **UI language:** English only for all user-facing strings
- **Stack:** Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Prisma, SQLite, shadcn/ui, Tailwind
- **Deployment:** Local-first; single workspace; no auth in MVP
- **Source of truth:** Read `docs/PLAN.md` and `AGENTS.md` before architectural changes

## Code style

- Strict TypeScript; no `any` without comment
- Zod for API input validation
- Prefer server components; use `"use client"` only when needed
- Colocate feature components under `src/components/<feature>/`

## Data access

- Prisma client singleton in `src/lib/db.ts`
- API routes return `{ data }` or `{ error: { code, message } }`

## Security

- Mask secret variables in UI and logs
- Do not expose SQLite file path in API responses
